Sports Analytics - Does it make a difference?

Salary Data - https://www.spotrac.com

TeamData <- read.csv("ESPNSportsAnalytics.csv")

colnames(TeamData)[1] <- "Sport"
TeamData %<>% mutate(PopulationMil = digits(Market/1e+06, 1))

TeamDataKM2015 <- TeamData %>% select(X2014HF, X2015HF)

TeamDataKM2016 <- TeamData %>% select(X2014HF, X2015HF, X2016HF)

TeamDataKM2017 <- TeamData %>% select(X2014HF, X2015HF, X2016HF, 
    X2017HF)

TeamDataKM2018 <- TeamData %>% select(X2014HF, X2015HF, X2016HF, 
    X2017HF, X2018HF)

TeamDataKM2019 <- TeamData %>% select(X2014HF, X2015HF, X2016HF, 
    X2017HF, X2018HF, X2019HF)

Overall

TeamDataNew <- TeamData %>% group_by(Team) %>% mutate(HowFar = sum(X2014HF, 
    X2015HF, X2016HF, X2017HF, X2018HF, X2019HF)/6)

# New team only last three years with 8 total for how far
TeamDataNew$HowFar[TeamDataNew$Team == "Golden Knights"] <- 8/3

TeamDataNewDT <- TeamDataNew %>% group_by(Sport) %>% summarise(count = n(), 
    MeanESPN = digits(mean(ESPNRating), 1), StdESPN = digits(sd(ESPNRating), 
        1)) %>% flextable() %>% bold(part = "header") %>% align(align = "center", 
    part = "header") %>% fontsize(size = 16, part = "all") %>% 
    autofit() %>% bg(bg = "white", part = "all")

UofArkPresNew <- UofArkPres %>% add_slide(master = "Black") %>% 
    ph_with(value = "Overview By Sport", location = ph_location_type(type = "title")) %>% 
    ph_with(TeamDataNewDT, location = ph_location(left = 3, top = 2))

K Means clustering 2019

TeamDataKM2019 <- scale(TeamDataKM2019)

fit <- kmeans(TeamDataKM2019, 2)

TeamDataKM2019 <- data.frame(TeamDataKM2019, fit$cluster)

TeamData2019 <- data.frame(TeamData, fit$cluster)

rownames(TeamData2019) <- paste(TeamData2019$Sport, TeamData2019$Team, 
    sep = "")

clusplot(TeamData2019, fit$cluster, color = TRUE, shade = FALSE, 
    labels = 2, lines = 0, cex.txt = 0.5, col.clus = c("red", 
        "green"), col.txt = c("black", "black"))

TeamData2019 %<>% rename(Cluster = fit.cluster)

TeamData2019DT <- TeamData2019 %>% group_by(Cluster) %>% summarise(Teams = n(), 
    MeanX2014HF = digits(mean(X2014HF), 1), MeanX2015HF = digits(mean(X2015HF), 
        1), MeanX2016HF = digits(mean(X2016HF), 1), MeanX2017HF = digits(mean(X2017HF), 
        1), MeanX2018HF = digits(mean(X2018HF), 1), MeanX2019HF = digits(mean(X2019HF), 
        1), MeanPopulation = digits(mean(PopulationMil), 1), 
    MeanSalary = digits(mean(X2019Salary), 1), MeanESPNRating = digits(mean(ESPNRating), 
        1))

# TeamData2019DT <- as.data.frame(t(TeamData2019DT))
# colnames(TeamData2019DT) <- c('1','2')

TeamData2019DTFT <- TeamData2019DT %>% flextable() %>% # colformat_num(digits = 1) %>%
bold(part = "header") %>% # align(align = 'center', part = 'header' ) %>%
fontsize(size = 12, part = "all") %>% rotate(rotation = "tbrl", 
    align = "center", part = "header") %>% align(align = "right", 
    part = "header") %>% valign(valign = "center", part = "header") %>% 
    align(align = "center", part = "body") %>% set_table_properties(width = 0.2, 
    layout = "autofit") %>% # autofit() %>%
height(height = 1.5, part = "header") %>% bg(bg = "white", part = "all") %>% 
    bg(j = 11, bg = "yellow", part = "all") %>% bg(j = 9:10, 
    bg = "green", part = "all")

K-Means Clustering 2017

TeamDataKM2017 <- scale(TeamDataKM2017)

fit <- kmeans(TeamDataKM2017, 2)

TeamDataKM2017 <- data.frame(TeamDataKM2017, fit$cluster)

TeamData2017 <- data.frame(TeamData, fit$cluster)

rownames(TeamData2017) <- paste(TeamData2017$Sport, TeamData2017$Team, 
    sep = "")

clusplot(TeamData2017, fit$cluster, color = TRUE, shade = FALSE, 
    labels = 2, lines = 0, cex.txt = 0.5, col.clus = c("red", 
        "green"), col.txt = c("black", "black"))

TeamData2017DT <- TeamData2017 %>% group_by(TeamData2017$fit.cluster) %>% 
    summarise(count = n(), MeanX2014HF = digits(mean(X2014HF), 
        1), MeanX2015HF = digits(mean(X2015HF), 1), MeanX2016HF = digits(mean(X2016HF), 
        1), MeanX2017HF = digits(mean(X2017HF), 1), MeanPopulation = digits(mean(PopulationMil), 
        1), MeanSalary = digits(mean(X2017Salary), 1), MeanESPNRating = digits(mean(ESPNRating), 
        1)) %>% flextable() %>% bold(part = "header") %>% fontsize(size = 12, 
    part = "all") %>% rotate(rotation = "tbrl", align = "center", 
    part = "header") %>% align(align = "right", part = "header") %>% 
    valign(valign = "center", part = "header") %>% align(align = "center",

ESPNAnalytics <- data.frame(Year = c(2015, 2016, 2017, 2018, 
    2019), High = c(3.5, 3.6, 3.8, 4, 4), Low = c(3.1, 3, 2.9, 
    2.9, 2.9))

ESPNAnalyticsTime <- ESPNAnalytics %>% ggplot() + geom_line(aes(x = Year, 
    y = High), color = "green", size = 1.5) + geom_line(aes(x = Year, 
    y = Low), color = "red", size = 1.5) + scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(2015, 
    2019, by = 1)) + scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 5)) + ylab("Mean K-Means Group ESPNAnalytics Score") + 
    theme(legend.position = "none", text = element_text(size = 50)) + 
    ggtitle("2015-2019 Gap Between High and Low ESPN Analytics Groups") + 
    theme_dark() + geom_label(aes(x = Year, y = High, label = paste(digits(High, 
    1))), bg = "green") + geom_label(aes(x = Year, y = Low, label = paste(digits(Low, 
    1))), bg = "red", color = "white")
